A powerful cyclone hit Bangladesh's southern coast, causing severe destruction.
Officials in both Bangladesh and India evacuated hundreds of thousands of people.
The storm, named Sidr, killed at least 41 people and forced the evacuation of 650,000 villagers.
The United States and Germany offered emergency relief aid.
The cyclone left a trail of devastation, with reports of rising death tolls.
The United Nations World Food Program allocated food to feed 400,000 victims.
Efforts are ongoing to provide shelter, clean water, and medical help to those affected.
The international community is working together to assist in the recovery process.
